trans-unit.source: Represents configuration settings that enable use of the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.BuildProvider"></xref> class for specific folders.
The ASP.NET build environment uses <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> objects to generate source code for different file types and subfolders in an application.

Classes that are derived from the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> class generate source code for folders such as Bin, App_GlobalResources, App_LocalResources, App_WebReferences, App_Browsers, Theme, and for other custom folders.
Typically, you do not create an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> class directly.

Instead, you implement a class that derives from <xref:System.Web.Compilation.BuildProvider> and apply the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.FolderLevelBuildProviderAppliesToAttribute> class to it, and then configure the derived class for use in the ASP.NET build environment.
The <xref:System.Web.Compilation.FolderLevelBuildProviderAppliesToAttribute> class targets folders instead of files.

You use instances of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> class together with <xref:System.Web.Compilation.AssemblyBuilder> objects to build one or more files into a compiled assembly.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> instance generates source code in the appropriate language for individual files, and the <xref:System.Web.Compilation.AssemblyBuilder> object builds the source code contributed by each <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> instance into a single assembly.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> class is specified in the `configuration` section of the Web.config file.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider"></xref> class by using an identifier and the fully qualified name.
The identifier for the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.BuildProvider"></xref> to use.
The fully qualified name of the <xref href="System.Web.Compilation.BuildProvider"></xref> to use.
Returns a value that indicates whether a specified object is equal to the current <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider"></xref> object.
The build provider object to compare.
`true` if the specified folder level build provider object is equal to the current object; otherwise, `false`.
Generates a hash code for the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider"></xref> object.
This method generates an integer that can be use to identify the folder level build provider object.
This method inherits from the <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A> method.
The <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A> method is suitable for hashing algorithms and data structures such as a hash table.
The hash code for the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider"></xref> object.
Gets or sets the name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider"></xref> object.
The name of the build provider object.
Gets or set the fully qualified name of the build provider class.
The fully qualified name of the build provider class.
